ēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alexander of Cawdor was born about 1105, in Elginshire, Scotland. He had at least 2 sons."},"et":{"about 1105–":"umbes 1105–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1105–Male":"1105–Surnud","1205":"1205","1105":"1105","about 1105":"umbes 1105","1140":"1140","Calder, Moray, Scotland":"Elginshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1105–":"noin 1105–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1105–Male":"1105–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1105":"1105","about 1105":"noin 1105","1140":"1140","Calder, Moray, Scotland":"Elginshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1105–":"environ 1105–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1205–Male":"1205–Décédé","1105–Male":"1105–Décédé","1205":"1205","1105":"1105","about 1105":"environ 1105","1140":"1140","Calder, Moray, Scotland":"Elginshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Alexander of Cawdor est né environ 1105, à Elginshire, Écosse. Il a eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"about 1105–":"um 1105–Verstorben","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","1205–Male":"1205–Verstorben","1105–Male":"1105–Verstorben","1205":"1205","1105":"1105","about 1105":"um 1105","1140":"1140","Calder, Moray, Scotland":"Elginshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Alexander of Cawdor wurde um 1105 in Elginshire, Scotland geboren. Er hatte mindestens 2 Söhne."},"ht":{"about 1105–":"about 1105–Desede","1140–Male":"1140–Desede","1205–Male":"1205–Desede","1105–Male":"1105–Desede","1205":"1205","1105":"1105","about 1105":"about 1105","1140":"1140","Calder, Moray, Scot